t-sure-why-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06321-z%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2056%25%20of%20the%20world's%3C%2Fa%3E%20oceans%20have%20seen%20significant%20changes%20in%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20is%20most%20dramatic%20in%20tropical%20oceans%2C%20which%20have%20become%20greener%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20per%20a%20study%20published%20in%20July%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20fear%20these%20color%20changes%20could%20be%20harbingers%20of%20yet%20another%20global%20crisis%20in%20ocean%20food%20chains%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperts-share-reasons-hopeful-climate-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%3Ethe%20planet%20warms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20gives%20additional%20evidence%20of%20how%20human%20activities%20are%20affecting%20life%20on%20Earth%20over%20a%20huge%20spatial%20extent%2C%26quot%3B%20B.B.%20Cael%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20National%20Oceanography%20Center%20in%20Southampton%2C%20UK%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mit.edu%2F2023%2Fstudy-oceans-color-changing-climate-change-0712%5C%22%3Ean%20author%20on%20the%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGreener%20oceans%20mean%20more%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20good%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20color%20of%20the%20oceans%20can%20tell%20us%20a%20lot%20about%20their%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20we%20care%20about%20this%20is%20not%20because%20we%20care%20about%20the%20color%2C%20but%20because%20the%20color%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20state%20of%20the%20ecosystem%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fjul%2F12%2Fworlds-oceans-changing-colour-due-to-climate-breakdown-study-suggests%5C%22%3Esaid%20Cael%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ocean's%20color%20depends%20on%20what's%20in%20the%20upper%20layer%20of%20the%20water%20column.%20A%20deep%20blue%20sea%20doesn't%20have%20not%20much%20life%20in%20that%20upper%20layer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20ocean%20turns%20green%2C%20however%2C%20that%20usually%20means%20the%20ocean%20is%20teeming%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-sea-phytoplankton-bloom-bosphorus-turquoise-photos-2017-6%5C%22%3Ephytoplankton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tiny%20organisms%20that%20can%20use%20sunlight%20to%20capture%20carbon%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20sugars%2C%20just%20like%20plants%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20latest%20study%2C%20scientists%20used%20imagery%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-fires-nasa-satellite-images-show-increased-carbon-monoxide-levels-2019-8%5C%22%3ENASA's%20Aqua%20satellite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20monitoring%20ocean%20color%20changes%20for%20more%20than%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20that%20while%20some%20oceans%20are%20getting%20marginally%20redder%20or%20bluer%2C%20most%20of%20the%20oceans%20that%20have%20seen%20a%20change%20in%20color%20are%20getting%20greener%2C%20which%20could%20mean%20more%20phytoplankton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20good%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20these%20plankton%20are%20crucial%20to%20marine%20ecosystems%20%E2%80%94%20they%20form%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhales-capture-carbon-climate-change-dying-pooping-2022-12%5C%22%3Ecomplex%20food%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20feeds%20everything%20from%20sea%20birds%20to%20whales%20%E2%80%94%20ocean%20ecosystems%20are%20very%20finely%20tuned%2C%20and%20any%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F07%2F12%2Fworld%2Fclimate-change-ocean-colors-scli-intl-scn%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520research%2520shows%2520that%2520our%2Cover%2520the%2520last%252020%2520years.%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520color%2520of%2520the%2520ocean%2Caccording%2520to%2520a%2520new%2520study.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echange%20to%20the%20ecosystem%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20ripple%20across%20the%20food%20chain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20changes%20are%20causing%20an%20imbalance%20in%20the%20natural%20organization%20of%20ecosystems.%20Such%20imbalance%20will%20only%20get%20worse%20over%20time%20if%20our%20oceans%20keep%20heating%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stephanie%20Dutkiewicz%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20MIT's%20Department%20of%20Earth%2C%20Atmospheric%20and%20Planetary%20Sciences%20and%20the%20Center%20for%20Global%20Change%20Science%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20study%2C%20to%20CNN.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EScientists%20are%20racing%20to%20understand%20why%20our%20oceans%20are%20fading%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20these%20changes%20are%20small%20and%20likely%20not%20big%20enough%20to%20cause%20a%20major%20overhaul%20of%20the%20food%20systems%2C%20said%20Cael%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%20Still%2C%20these%20results%20are%20%26quot%3Bsobering%2C%26quot%3B%20Dutkiewicz%2C%20told%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20running%20simulations%20that%20have%20been%20telling%20me%20for%20years%20that%20these%20changes%20in%20ocean%20color%20are%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BTo%20actually%20see%20it%20happening%20for%20real%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20but%20frightening%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20will%20now%20try%20to%20understand%20exactly%20what%20is%20causing%20the%20changes%20in%20color%20to%20better%20predict%20how%20our%20oceans%20could%20evolve%20as%20the%20planet%20gets%20warmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20likely%2C%20it%20will%20come%20down%20to%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20factors%20changing%20in%20parallel%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20J%20Behrenfeld%2C%20a%20researcher%20of%20ocean%20productivity%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%2C%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%