his%20as-told-to%20story%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20an%20anonymous%20tech%20worker%20in%20their%2040s.%20Insider%20verified%20their%20employment%20and%20is%20withholding%20their%20name%20to%20protect%20their%20employment.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20full-time%20as%20the%20content%20director%20for%20a%20New%20York-based%20tech%20startup%20for%20about%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years.%20The%20job%20is%20convenient%20because%20I%20can%20work%20remotely%20from%20my%20home%20in%20LA%2C%20but%20otherwise%2C%20I'm%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrumpy-stayers-people-stuck-in-jobs-cant-leave-quiet-quitting-2023-7%5C%22%3Egrumpy%20stayer%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20because%20I'm%20not%20completely%20happy%20with%20my%20work%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20much%20rather%20work%20as%20a%20full-time%20freelance%20writer%20and%20digital%20nomad.%20However%2C%20once%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20many%20of%20my%20projects%20dried%20up%2C%20and%20in%20April%202020%2C%20I%20took%20a%20full-time%20position%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20a%20grumpy%20stayer%20who's%20become%20more%20vocal%20about%20my%20unhappiness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20tech%20startup%2C%20I%20oversee%20a%20content%20schedule%20much%20like%20a%20magazine%20would%20work.%20We%20create%20content%20to%20match%20our%20sales%20goals%2C%20and%20I%20help%20plan%20and%20manage%20the%20project%20and%20writers%20from%20start%20to%20finish.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20become%20more%20assertive%20in%20my%2040s%2C%20which%20management%20doesn't%20always%20appreciate.%20HR%20and%20the%20executive%20team%20don't%20like%20that%20I'm%20an%20advocate%20and%20likely%20see%20me%20as%20grumpy%20or%20difficult%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20if%20we're%20given%20unreasonably%20tight%20deadlines%2C%20I'll%20openly%20address%20the%20entire%20team%2C%20including%20my%20boss%2C%20explaining%20why%20such%20timelines%20are%20unfair.%20I%20advise%20my%20co-workers%20to%20disregard%20emails%20and%20requests%20beyond%20working%20hours%20and%20encourage%20them%20to%20voice%20their%20concerns%20if%20the%20workload%20becomes%20overwhelming.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20advocate%20for%20my%20co-workers.%20For%20example%2C%20at%20our%20last%20team%20meeting%2C%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20talk%20about%20what's%20going%20well%20and%20what's%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20then%20everybody%20is%20just%20sitting%20there%20looking%20at%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20I'll%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20meetings%2C%20I've%20pointed%20out%20that%20my%20team%20excelled%20at%20our%20work%2C%20which%20is%20why%20we%20deserve%20a%20raise.%26quot%3B%20I've%20often%20raised%20the%20topic%20of%20pay%20during%20meetings%20and%20encouraged%20colleagues%20to%20push%20for%20salary%20increases.%20When%20you%20speak%20up%2C%20others%20see%20it's%20okay%20and%20feel%20more%20comfortable%20voicing%20their%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagement%20gives%20us%20the%20runaround.%20For%20many%20years%2C%20we've%20been%20told%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20tight%20on%20the%20budget%2C%20but%20we'd%20love%20you%20to%20step%20up%20and%20do%20more.%26quot%3B%20There's%20a%20vague%20promise%20of%20potential%20promotions%20in%20the%20future%2C%20asking%20us%20to%20do%20more%20and%20have%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20raises%2C%20this%20year%20it%20was%20across%20the%20board%2C%20%26quot%3BNo.%26quot%3B%20Higher-ups%20told%20us%20we%20had%20a%20very%20bad%20year%20and%20didn't%20hit%20our%20sales%20goals.%20I%20argued%20that%20this%20had%20little%20to%20do%20with%20my%20team's%20work%3B%20we%20hit%2098%25%20of%20our%20goals.%20But%20they%20countered%20that%20the%20market%20and%20product%20we're%20selling%20changed%2C%20resulting%20in%20lower%20sales%2C%20which%20has%20nothing