0he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-living-at-home-as-an-adult-2023-1%5C%22%3Elived%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20his%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20a%20year%2C%20he'd%20saved%20up%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20down%20payment%20on%20a%20%24262%2C000%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fhomedetails%2F228-W-Fulton-St-Stockton-CA-95204%2F15313365_zpid%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Stockton%2C%20California.%20It%20was%2091%20years%20old%20and%20about%201%2C500%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20cultural%20background%20that%20emphasized%20hard%20work%20and%20strong%20discipline%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20financed%20my%20first%20home%20entirely%20from%20my%20two%20jobs.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20rather%20than%20moving%20into%20this%20new%20home%2C%20Chaw%20said%20he%20decided%20to%20keep%20living%20with%20his%20parents%20and%20rent%20it%20out.%20As%20of%202022%2C%20he%20was%20earning%20over%20%242%2C500%20per%20month%20from%20four%20tenants%2C%20according%20to%20a%20document%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%C2%A0He%20paid%20off%20the%20home%20in%202021%20and%20this%20past%20April%2C%20sold%20the%20property%20for%20about%20%24437%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20all%20my%20money%20back%20and%20then%20much%2C%20much%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20high%20housing%20prices%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-mortgage-rates-low-inventory-listings-homes-for-sale-2023-6%5C%22%3Ehigh%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20put%20buying%20a%20home%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20many%20young%20Americans.%20Last%20November%2C%20the%20typical%20first-time%20homebuyer%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fnewsroom%2Fnar-finds-share-of-first-time-home-buyers-smaller-older-than-ever-before%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E36%20years%20old%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20all-time%20high%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20these%20challenges%2C%20many%20young%20people%20have%20found%20a%20way%20to%20attain%20homeownership%20before%20the%20age%20of%2030.%20As%20of%202021%2C%2029%25%20of%20US%2018-29-year-olds%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fpublications%2F2022-economic-well-being-of-us-households-in-2021-housing.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowned%20their%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20compared%20to%2061%25%20of%2030-44-year-olds.%20While%20some%20young%20Americans%20have%20relied%20on%20parental%20support%20to%20reach%20this%20milestone%2C%20others%20have%20saved%20money%2C%20boosted%20their%20credit%20scores%2C%20or%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-buy-a-house-in-your-20s-gen-z-2022-3%5C%22%3Egovernment%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20this%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20rookie%20mistake%20that%20new%20homebuyers%20should%20avoid%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Chaw%20largely%20views%20his%20first%20homebuying%20experience%20as%20a%20success%20story%2C%20he%20said%20he%20made%20one%20costly%20mistake.%20After%20purchasing%20the%20Stockton%20home%2C%20which%20was%20built%20in%201925%2C%20he%20discovered%20there%20were%20roughly%20%2430%2C000%20in%20unexpected%20repairs.%20These%20included%20roughly%20%2417%2C000%20to%20replace%20the%20HVAC%20system%2C%20%244%2C700%20for%20plumbing%20cleanup%20and%20the%20replacement%20of%20a%20sewage%20line%2C%20%241%2C700%20to%20address%20a%20rat%20infestation%20problem%2C%20and%20%242%2C600%20to%20install%20a%20new%20water%20heater.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20do%20my%20due%20diligence%20to%20figure%20out%20if%20there%20were%20major%20issues%20with%20the%20property%20before%20buying%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BAlways%20get%20a%20house%20inspection%20done%20before%20making%20a%20purchasing%20decision%3B%20it%20can%20save%20you%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20he%20was%20in%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20bind%2C%20Chaw%20said%20his%20father%20agreed%20to%20cover%20roughly%20%2423%2C000%20of%20these%20repair%20expenses.%20In%20return%2C%20Chaw%20said%20he%20agreed%20to%20give%20his%20father%20%24550%20per%20month%20%E2%80%94%20the%20monthly%20rent%20of%20one%20of%20the%20tenants%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%20He's%20continued%20giving%20his%20father%20this%20money%20even%20though%20the%20property%20was%20sold%20in%20April.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChaw%20said%20this%20experience%20helped%20him%20become%20a%20better%20real%20estate%20investor.%20In%20August%2C%20he%20quit%20his%20pharmacist%20job%20of%20over%20seven%20years%20to%20focus%20exclusively%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstrategies-real-estate-investor-get-started-2022-4%5C%22%3Emanaging%20his%20rental%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20he%20owns%20several%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Chaw%20decided%20to%20move%20out%20of%20his%20parent's%20home%20to%20a%20house%20in%20Sacramento%20he%20purchased%2C%20but%20he%20didn't%20stop%20having%20tenants.%20He's%20currently%20using%20a%20strategy%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhouse-hacking%5C%22%3Ehouse%20hacking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20homeowner%20lives%20in%20their%20house%20and%20rents%20out%20spare%20rooms%20to%20help%20pay%20down%20their%20mortgage.%20Chaw%20said%20he%20lives%20with%20four%20housemates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20I%20see%20it%2C%20my%20%2410%2C000%20mistakes%20save%20me%20from%20making%20%24100%2C000%2