est%20in%20how%20you%20behave%20with%20your%20current%20partner.%20Often%20these%20patterns%20start%20early%2C%20in%20relationships%20you%20had%20with%20your%20parents%20growing%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20childhood%20experiences%20with%20our%20parents%20and%20our%20teachers%20and%20our%20friends%20really%20do%20have%20a%20pretty%20big%20impact%20on%20how%20we%20operate%20both%20personally%20and%20professionally%20in%20early%20adulthood%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20B.%20Rhodes%2C%20a%20psychologist%2C%20dating%20coach%2C%20and%20founder%20of%20Rapport%20Relationships%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20pretty%20big%20population%20of%20people%20who%20enter%20early%20adulthood%20who%20have%20insecurity%20around%20creating%20and%20managing%20relationships.%20So%20I%20think%20what%20happens%20is%20when%20you're%20not%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20patterns%20you%20experienced%20at%20a%20younger%20age%2C%20you%20actually%20reenact%20those%20as%20an%20adult%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20it%20doesn't%20look%20pretty%20in%20your%20personal%20or%20your%20professional%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spoke%20to%20several%20relationship%20experts%20to%20find%20out%20how%20to%20tell%20if%20you're%20still%20hanging%20on%20to%20your%20past%2C%20and%20how%20this%20affects%20your%20current%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1.%20You%20always%20attract%20the%20same%20type%20of%20people%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20hugging%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef25d096b7920019ca4b84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EImage%20Source%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Judith%20Orloff%2C%20a%20psychiatrist%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Empath's%20Survival%20Guide%3A%20Life%20Strategies%20for%20Sensitive%20People%2C%26quot%3B%20if%20one%20of%20your%20parents%20was%20a%20narcissist%2C%20or%20an%20alcoholic%2C%20you%20may%20find%20you%20keep%20being%20attracted%20to%20these%20types%20of%20people%20until%20you%20can%20work%20through%20what%20hurt%20you%20in%20that%20initial%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmpaths%20do%20this%20a%20lot%2C%20because%20they're%20such%20fixers%20and%20they%20want%20to%20get%20in%20there%20and%20heal%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20think%20if%20they%20fix%20the%20person%2C%20somehow%20that's%20going%20to%20heal%20their%20original%20relationship.%20But%20it%20never%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20important%20that%20people%20are%20aware%2C%20if%20they've%20had%20alcoholic%20parents%20and%20they%20keep%20attracting%20alcoholic%20boyfriends%2C%20that%20there%20may%20be%20a%20connection%20there%2C%20and%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20into%20whatever%20wounds%20you%20had%20growing%20up%20with%20an%20alcoholic%20parent%20so%20you%20don't%20keep%20creating%20that%20in%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E2.%20You%20have%20'tainted%20joys'%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20sleeping%2C%20feeling%20sad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef2c4896b7920019ca4f0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFiordaliso%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPerpetua%20Neo%2C%20a%20doctor%20of%20psychology%20and%20who%20runs%20a%20therapy%20program%20called%20Detox%20Your%20Heart%2C%20told%20Insider%20a%20bad%20relationship%20can%20give%20you%20%26quot%3Btainted%20pleasures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20things%20or%20experiences%20that%20were%20once%20important%20to%20you%2C%20or%20that%20you%20used%20to%20enjoy%2C%20but%20you%20now%20can't%20stand%20because%20they%20are%20connected%20to%20your%20previous%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOr%20you%20feel%20guilty%20for%20enjoying%20it%2C%20or%20revisiting%20the%20same%20thing%20re-traumatizes%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRe-trauma%20can%20be%20something%20normal%2C%20but%20having%20it%20persist%20for%20a%20long%20time%20is%20not%20normal.%20There's%20a%20big%20distinction.%20There's%20always%20this%20period%20of%20healing%20where%20you%20get%20this%20dip%20and%20after%20that%20you%20get%20a%20rise.%20But%20if%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20always%20going%20to%20be%20in%20this%20dip%20forever%2C%20then%20that's%20not%20healthy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETainted%20pleasures%20can%20be%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20a%20musician%20or%20a%20place.%20It%20could%20even%20be%20an%20item%20of%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20wear%20this%20dress%2C%20not%20because%20he%20bought%20it%20for%20me%2C%20but%20because%20he%20said%20something%20nice%20about%20it%20or%20I%20wore%20it%20to%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Neo%20said%20as%20an%20example.%20%26quot%3BSo%20sometimes%20there's%20this%20guilt%20that%20you're%20betraying%20your%20ex-partner%2C%20and%20sometimes%20you%20just%20feel%20like%20it's%20been%20tainted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E3.%20You%20have%20hangups%20around%20physical%20intimacy%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22couple%20in%20bed%2C%20unhappy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef269496b7920019ca4bc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPhotoAlto%2FFrederic%20Cirou%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20the%20signs%20might%20not%20be%20apparent%20until%20you're%20in%20the%20bedroom.%20Neo%20said%20people%20can%20have%20sexual%20hangups%20around%20their%20previous%20relationships%20for%20various%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20instance%2C%20when%20people%20feel%20they%20cannot%20be%20sexually%20intimate%20because%20of%20their%20ex-partner%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20just%20talking%20about%20general%20sex%2C%20but%20also%20certain%20positions%2C%20or%20certain%20ways%20in%20which%20a%20person%20touches%20them%2C%20or%20how%20they%20see%20themselves%20sensually.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20sign%20is%20if%20you%20have%20to%20say%20to%20yourself%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20think%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20try%20and%20wipe%20it%20from%20your%20mind%2C%20Neo%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20it%20still%20owns%20you%20emotionally%2C%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%2C%20or%20if%20you're%20triggered%20or%20stressed%2C%20then%20it%20still%20affects%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E4.%20You%20haven't%20figured%20out%20your%20attachment%20style%20yet%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20arguing%20in%20bedroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef2daebdd7e70019dfd143%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EOlga%20Rolenko%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthe-3-different-attachment-styles-2018-6%5C%22%3Efour%20different%20attachment%20styles%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20secure%2C%20anxious%2C%20avoidant-dismissive%2C%20and%20and%20fearful-avoidant.%20Some%20people%20may%20not%20be%20ready%20to%20delve%20into%20the%20past%20and%20figure%20out%20their%20patterns%2C%20so%20they%20bring%20all%20their%20past%20errors%20along%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20haven't%20figured%20out%20which%20attachment%20style%20we%20have%2C%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20move%20onto%20a%20new%20relationship%20in%20a%20healthy%20way%20because%20we%20may%20repeat%20the%20same%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPsychotherapist%20Emily%20Morehead%20told%20Insider%20that%20attachment%20style%20%26quot%3Bplays%20into%20every%20relationship%20that%20we%20have%20and%20honestly%20how%20we%20view%20other%20humans%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20relationships%2C%20workplaces%2C%20parenting%2C%20sexuality%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20root%20of%20the%20problem%20does%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20links%20to%20that%20attachment%20style%20and%20those%20early%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20therapy%20that%20we%20do%20is%20helping%20people%20feel%20strong%20enough%20and%20brave%20enough%20to%20believe%20that%20they're%20worthy%20of%20learning%20that%20about%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorehead%20said%20healing%20comes%20when%20people%20become%20%26quot%3Breally%20curious%26quot%3B%20about%20themselves%2C%20and%20learn%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20detective%20on%20your%20own%20behaviors%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20questioning%20why%20they%20get%20triggered%20by%20certain%20things%2C%20recognizing%20their%20patterns%2C%20and%20understanding%20their%20own%20needs%2C%20such%20as%20needing%20a%20nap%2C%20a%20break%2C%20or%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20trusted%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBreaking%20it%20down%20to%20that%20basic%20level%20physiological%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20your%20body's%20regulated%2C%20you%20can%20understand%20the%20emotion%20and%20experience%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E5.%20You%20struggle%20to%20communicate%20about%20things%20that%20upset%20you%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225973%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20standing%20argues%20with%20another%20person%20sitting%20on%20a%20couch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef26d4bdd7e70019dfcd30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMarko%20Geber%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Brud%C3%B6%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20the%20personal-development%20and%20mental-well-being%20app%20Remente%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20an%20inability%20to%20communicative%20effectively%20can%20can%20form%20as%20a%20result%20of%20a%20bad%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20felt%20that%20you%20weren't%20listened%20to%20in%20a%20previous%20relationship%2C%20your%20way%20of%20communicating%20might%20be%20more%20aggressive%20than%20necessary%20in%20the%20new%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20resentment%20building%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20psychologist%20Linda%20Blair%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BStraight%20Talking%26quot%3B%20and%20several%20other%20books%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20say%20early%20on%20that%20something%20bothers%20you%2C%20it's%20only%20when%20it%20gets%20to%20a%20fight%20that%20grievances%20are%20actually%20voiced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDid%20I%20say%20early%20enough%20on%20that%20that%20bothers%20me%3F%20Or%20did%20I%20wait%2C%20hoping%20it%20would%20go%20away%2C%20until%20it%20got%20so%20bad%20it%20caused%20a%20row%20between%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BResentment%20is%20often%20a%20potential%20flashpoint.%20Lack%20of%20communication%20about%20plans%2C%20that's%20also%20often%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E6.%20Your%20wounds%20are%20not%20healed%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22couple%20standing%20either%20side%20of%20a%20tree%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef273796b7920019ca4c33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJon%20Vallejo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20people%20mimic%20the%20bad%20communication%20they%20had%20in%20previous%20relationships%2C%20this%20can%20easily%20lead%20to%20fierce%20rows%2C%20according%20to%20Orloff.%20People%20have%20emotional%20buttons%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20this%20could%20be%20anything%20that%20upsets%20them%20%E2%80%94%20words%2C%20a%20tone%20of%20voice%2C%20or%20shaming%20%E2%80%94%20and%20these%20are%20where%20your%20wounds%20are.%