C%20deserts%2C%20seas%2C%20oceans%20%E2%80%93%20you%20name%20it.%20My%20only%20wish%20is%20to%20feast%20my%20eyes%20on%20them.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20initial%20reaction%20of%20his%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%20thought%20that%20I%20had%20lost%20my%20mind%20and%20were%20pretty%20sure%20that%20I%20would%20quit%20after%20two%20days%20of%20walking.%20But%2C%20I%20did%20it.%20I%20walked%20for%208%20days%20and%20reached%20Kedarnath.%20The%20feeling%20is%20indescribable%20as%20I%20was%20so%20overwhelmed%20by%20what%20I%20had%20achieved.%20I%20knew%20then%20that%20I%20would%20not%20stop%20now.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYati%20has%20also%20been%20documenting%20his%20journey%20on%20Instagram%20and%20has%20an%20earnest%20following%20of%2053%2C319%20thousand%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20have%20been%20loving%20our%20journey%20together%20and%20some%20brands%20have%20been%20generous%20enough%20to%20sponsor%20us.%20There%20is%20a%20UP-based%20gentleman%20who%20sponsored%20Buttercup%E2%80%99s%20food%20for%20the%20Chardham%20journey%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20childhood%20we%20have%20all%20heard%20our%20fathers%20and%20grandfathers%20brag%20and%20say%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eduniya%20dekhi%20hai%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(I%20have%20seen%20the%20world)%2C%20well%2C%20with%20such%20diversity%20in%20India%2C%20they%20might%20have%20just%20peeked%20through%20the%20keyhole%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20door.%20However%2C%20not%20for%20Yati%2C%20as%20he%20and%20Buttercup%20have%20literally%20been%20seeing%20the%20world%2C%20one%20town%20at%20a%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693404383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fyati-1693402264.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D328577%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Interested%20in%20slow%20travel%20and%20cultures%20across%20India%2C%20Yati%20Gaur%20decided%20to%20walk%20through%20the%20country.%20He%20has%20completed%20five%20walking%20expeditions%20covering%20states%20such%20as%20Goa%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%20with%20his%20rescue%20dog%2C%20Buttercup.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F328577%2Fyati-gaur-from-uttar-pradesh-explores-india-on-foot-with-rescue-dog-travel-plans%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'It%20was%20like%20losing%20a%20family%20member'%3A%20The%20US%20soldier%20who%20cried%20after%20Saddam%20Hussein's%20execution%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693401360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-adam-rogerson-saddam_6268423.jpg%3F20230902075816%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fit-was-like-losing-a-family-member-the-us-soldier-who-cried-after-saddam-husseins-execution-12950837%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20August%202006%2C%20Specialist%20Adam%20Rogerson%20was%20standing%20metres%20away%20from%20Saddam%20Hussein%20as%20he%20slept%20in%20his%20cell%20beneath%20the%20Iraqi%20High%20Tribunal%20building%20in%20Baghdad.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fit-was-like-losing-a-family-member-the-us-soldier-who-cried-after-saddam-husseins-execution-12950837%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fit-was-like-losing-a-family-member-the-us-soldier-who-cried-after-saddam-husseins-execution-12950837%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fit-was-like-losing-a-family-member-the-us-soldier-who-cried-after-saddam-husseins-execution-12950837%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20Nature-Based%20Solutions%20That%20Are%20Making%20Low-Income%20Communities%20Resilient%20to%20Climate%20Change%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDr%20Pramila%20Sanjaya%20has%20lived%20in%20Jaipur%20for%20over%2060%20years.%20Through%20this%20time%2C%20she%20has%20watched%20the%20city%20grow%20and%20expand%20over%20existing%20villages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20used%20to%20be%20farms%20have%20now%20been%20converted%20into%20colonies%20and%20taken%20over%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F291949%2Fmumbai-urban-gardener-grows-passion-fruits-and-beekeeps-on-terrace-garden-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultistory%20buildings%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20I%20have%20also%20witnessed%20is%20the%20growth%20of%20informal%20settlements%20and%20slums%20across%20the%20city%2C%20which%20did%20not%20exist%20during%20my%20childhood.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrateek%20Tiwari%2C%20another%20Jaipur%20resident%20and%20CEO%20of%C2%A0%20Living%20Greens%20Organics%20Pvt.%20Ltd%2C%20also%20recalls%20a%20time%20when%20the%20city%20centre%20was%20full%20of%20trees.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%E2%80%99d%20visit%20my%20grandparents%20in%20Jaipur%20during%20May%2C%20summers%20weren%E2%80%99t%20something%20we%20would%20dread.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%E2%80%99d%20stay%20indoors%20between%2011%20am%20and%203%20pm%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it%20was%20very%20hot%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20temperature%20would%20drop%20and%20it%20would%20be%20pleasantly%20cool%2C%20enough%20for%20us%20to%20sleep%20on%20the%20terrace%20at%20night.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20no%20longer%20have%20those%20spaces%20that%20helped%20keep%20the%20city%20cool.%20Jaipur%20has%20changed%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20for%20the%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20opines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaipur%20is%20only%20one%20among%20the%20several%20Indian%20cities%20facing%20rising%20incidents%20of%20extreme%20heat%20and%20water%20scarcity.%20Meanwhile%2C%20coastal%20cities%20like%20Kochi%20and%20Mumbai%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F236067%2Fgurgaon-gurugram-urban-flooding-rains-monsoon-ghata-lake-bunds-dams-disappear-environment-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20with%20urban%20flooding%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Frequent%20heat%20waves%20and%20urban%20heat%20islands%20trap%20heat%20in%20neighbourhoods%2C%20giving%20residents%20little%20relief%2C%20even%20at%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ayyankali%20workers%20preparing%20the%20land%20to%20plant%20saplings%5Cn%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328525%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECoastal%20cities%20like%20Kochi%20and%20Mumbai%20are%20struggling%20with%20urban%20flooding.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeat%20impacts%20vulnerable%20communities%20the%20most%20due%20to%20the%20usage%20of%20unsuitable%20housing%20material%20such%20as%20tin%20sheets%20and%20lack%20of%20green%20cover.%20In%20Mumbai%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fmumbai-news%2Fmumbai-slums-are-6-degrees-celsius-warmer-than-neighbouring-housing-societies-in-october-study%2Fstory-wo22fMA4bIUjzvV5OIdamN.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslums%20in%20Dharavi%20are%20almost%206%20degrees%20hotter%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20better-shaded%20and%20more%20affluent%20neighbouring%20locality%20of%20Matunga.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20scenario%2C%20working%20with%20low-income%20neighbourhoods%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20high%20vulnerability%20to%20heat%20and%20flooding%20has%20become%20imperative.%20With%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20The%20World%20Resources%20Institute%20(WRI)%20India%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1838002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiloting%20different%20Nature-based%20solutions%20(NbS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20aimed%20at%20making%20communities%20more%20resilient%20to%20climate%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENbS%20interventions%20not%20only%20improve%20urban%20environmental%20ecosystems%2C%20but%20also%20offer%20social%20and%20economic%20benefits%20to%20communities%20by%20creating%20healthy%20spaces%20for%20recreation%2C%20and%20by%20opening%20up%20opportunities%20for%20skilling%20up%20and%20livelihood%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20are%20low-income%20groups%20so%20much%20more%20vulnerable%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Pramila%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20a%20community%20organiser%20and%20advisor%20at%20SIDART%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20works%20for%20the%20upliftment%20of%20women%20and%20children%20%E2%80%94%20says%20that%20water%20scarcity%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20flooding%20during%20monsoons%20has%20now%20become%20extremely%20common.%20%E2%80%9CUrbanisation%20has%20impacted%20natural%20biodiversity%2C%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20forests%20and%20hills%20being%20cut%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20rising%20fluctuations%20and%20climatic%20changes%20affect%20low-income%20groups%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20socio-economic%20and%20demographic%20factors.%20During%20the%202005%20Mumbai%20floods%2C%20over%20a%20million%20slum%20residents%20were%20stranded.%20These%20are%20the%20neighbourhoods%20that%20often%20lack%20access%20to%20basic%20services%20and%20amenities%20like%20potable%20water%2C%20energy%2C%20sanitation.%20For%20instance%2C%2084.9%25%20of%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20M-East%20ward%20population%20lives%20in%20slums%2C%20and%20only%2053.6%25%20of%20these%20households%20have%20access%20to%20water%20on%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328543%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20slums%20in%20Dharavi%20are%20almost%206%20degrees%20hotter%20than%20the%20better-shaded%20and%20more%20affluent%20neighbouring%20locality%20of%20Matunga.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffi